Our world faces a common enemy: #COVID19. Yet, armed conflict is hampering efforts to defeat the virus. 

@antonioguterres has called for a global ceasefire to reduce suffering &amp; strengthen pandemic recovery efforts. https://t.co/T5sln4KRN7

https://t.co/etGjTSkfAE

“Attacks on schools &amp; other educational facilities are abhorrent &amp; unacceptable.” 

@antonioguterres strongly condemns attack on school in Nigeria which resulted in death of one student and abduction of other school children, relatives &amp; staff.  
https://t.co/hveqpoWKra

It’s time to make #PeaceWithNature and tackle the climate, biodiversity &amp; pollution crises together. 

@UNEP explains how everyone has an urgent part to play to solve planetary emergencies &amp; secure humanity’s future: https://t.co/Oe96AxDEM2 #ClimateAction
https://t.co/C8pwr9z5Cv

Gender equality is necessary for a peaceful, prosperous &amp; sustainable world.
@UN_Women has ideas about how we can all speak up &amp; take action to achieve #GenerationEquality. https://t.co/IN3RJhmJq9

 https://t.co/jVNquWmfFA

“We had no choice but to run for our lives."

Pregnant women, like 24-year-old Hiwot, are among those who have fled Ethiopia's Tigray region amid intensified fighting.

@UNFPA supports them with reproductive health care &amp; psychosocial services. https://t.co/f36cJ0aBHF

Advances in the digital economy, accelerated by the #COVID19 crisis, are creating unprecedented opportunities for people with disabilities.

@ilo proposes actions to ensure that the post-pandemic world of work is more inclusive.

https://t.co/LERt7pKGLN

A new Ebola outbreak has been declared in southern Guinea, with at least seven people infected.

@WHO is on the ground, stepping up efforts to curb further infections of the deadly disease.

https://t.co/x947yixKo8
